@@@ [u' \xa0 Several prominent politicians and political commentators were born nine months after the 1947 Roswell "UFO" incident.\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n\r\n', u'\r\n\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n', u' \r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n', u' \xa0 This amusing bit of political humor first hit our inbox in ', u' positing a connection between ', u' events in Roswell, ', u' \r\n\r\n', u'\r\n\r\n(i.e., the alleged recovery of a crashed alien spacecraft and its occupants) and the birth nine months later of several prominent Democratic political figures.\r\n', u"\r\nAt the risk of belaboring the obvious by deconstructing humor, we'll point out that the basic premise of the joke doesn't ring true.  First of all, the normal human gestation period is about ", u' so children conceived on or shortly after the date of the Roswell incident ', u' 1947) would most likely have been born (assuming ordinary, full-term pregnancies) in April 1948, not March.  Second, only one of the political figures named was born even approximately nine months after the events as Roswell.  \r\n', u'\r\nFive of the people listed were born well before ', u'\r\n\r\n', u'\r\n\r\nTwo more of the persons identified were born considerably later than nine months after Roswell:\r\n\r\n', u'\r\n\r\nHillary Rodham Clinton (U.S. Senator, New York) was born on ', u' 1947, a mere three months after the Roswell incident.\r\n', u'\r\nOnly Al Gore, Jr. (former U.S. Vice-President), who was born on ', u' 1948, came into the world at a time that reasonably fits into the framework of this humorous premise.  Quite possibly this item started out as a joke specifically about him, and others later expanded it into a joke about Democrats in general.\r\n', u'\r\nIn April 2007, the jape was reworked to aim it at prominent Republicans and conservative pundits.  Four of the figures named on that list were born well before ', u'\r\n\r\n', u'\r\n\r\nThree others were born considerably later than nine months after Roswell:\r\n\r\n', u'