 Where does a \r\nreasonable standard of protection leave off and lunacy begin? Granted, if bullets are on the banned list then passengers shouldn't attempt to bring them onboard, but should bullets which have been drilled and turned into key charms \u2014 ornamental objects which clearly pose no threat to ", u' treated as if they were "real" bullets?  And should a Medal of Honor \u2014 the country\'s highest award for ', u' fleetingly be considered a possible threat to the safety of others?\r\n', u"\r\nUnfortunately, Joe Foss didn't have much time to ponder the rationale behind new airline travel restrictions after his January 2002 experience.  He passed away in an Arizona hospital at the age of 87 on ", u' Day of 2003.\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\nBarbara "perfect alibi" Mikkelson\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n\r\n', u'\r\n\r\n', u' \xa0 7 June 2014\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n'] @@@
