nd pursued a civil lawsuit against the comedian,  who maintained that he merely gave Constand some Benadryl tablets and that any subsequent sexual contact between them was consensual:\r\n\r\n', u"\r\n\r\nConstand's lawsuit referenced thirteen women who had alleged similar experiences with Cosby as Jane Doe witnesses, which is where the specific claim that the sitcom star has sexually assaulted thirteen different women originated.  Cosby settled the case with Constand in November 2006 (the terms of that settlement were not disclosed), so none of those thirteen other women was called to testify.\r\n", u"\r\nShortly after Constand's accusations went public, a second woman \u2014 a California lawyer by the name of Tamara Green \u2014 came forward and appeared on the ", u' show to assert that Cosby had acted similarly towards her back in the 1970s:\r\n\r\n', u"\r\n\r\nCosby denied Green's accusations, and no criminal charges or civil lawsuits resulted from her claims.\r\n", u"\r\nIn mid-2005 Beth Ferrier, the woman referenced as Jane Doe No. 5 in Andrea Constand's lawsuit against Cosby, also came forward to recount her claims of being drugged and sexually assaulted by the comedian:\r\n\r\n", u"\r\n\r\nAgain, no criminal charges or civil lawsuits resulted from Ferrier's claims.\r\n", u"\r\nAnother of the Jane Doe witnesses cited in Andrea Constand's lawsuit, Barbara Bowman, also came forward in 2006 and presented an account of being drugged and sexually assaulted:\r\n\r\n", u'\r\n\r\nAs ', u" magazine reported at the end of 2006 of all these women's allegations, none of the purported sexual assault incidents was reported to police, the statute of limitations on related criminal charges has expired, and several of the women accepted payments from Cosby and/or maintained consensual relationships with him afterwards:\r\n\r\n", u'\r\n\r\nThe allegations about Cosby surfaced again in February 2014 after Dylan Farrow wrote an open letter accusing her adoptive father Woody Allen of sexual abuse.  When Farrow\'s statement sparked a conversation about "forgetting" such accusations, ', u"'s Tom Scocca surmised Cosby's venerated position in popular culture and the public's unwillingness to change their perceptions of a beloved persona had shielded him from backlash:\r\n\r\n", u'\r\n\r\n', u' \xa0 24 October 2014\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n', u'\r\n'] @@@
